# Code Style Preferences

## Formatting & Organization
- Follow standard Rust conventions (rustfmt defaults)
- Group imports: std, external crates, local modules
- Use `//` comments for brief explanations, `///` for doc comments
- Prefer explicit types when learning (I'll remove them once comfortable)

## Code Organization
```
src/
├── main.rs           # App entry point and plugin registration
├── lib.rs            # Optional: library interface
├── plugins/          # Feature plugins
│   ├── mod.rs
│   ├── player.rs
│   ├── enemies.rs
│   └── ui.rs
├── components/       # Component definitions
├── systems/          # System functions  
├── resources/        # Resource definitions
└── events/           # Event definitions
```

## Naming Conventions
- Components: noun (e.g., `Player`, `Velocity`, `Health`)
- Systems: verb_noun (e.g., `move_player`, `spawn_enemies`, `handle_collisions`)
- Events: noun_verb (e.g., `PlayerDied`, `LevelCompleted`)
- Resources: noun (e.g., `GameState`, `ScoreBoard`)

## Useful Commands
```bash
cargo run                    # Run the game
cargo run --release          # Run optimized
cargo clippy                 # Linting
cargo doc --open            # Generate docs
```
